  "instructions": [
    "Place minced lamb shank into a chilled bowl.",
    "Whisk together canola oil, soy sauce, Dijon mustard, and lemon juice until a smooth emulsion forms.",
    "Pour the emulsion over the lamb and mix gently with a fork until fully incorporated.",
    "Fold in diced red onion, capers, and chopped dill.",
    "Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste.",
    "Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to allow flavors to meld.",
    "Before serving, give the mixture a final stir and adjust seasoning if necessary.",
    "Spoon the tartare into individual glasses or onto chilled plates.",
    "Garnish with a sprig of dill or a drizzle of extra lemon juice.",
    "Serve immediately chilled."
  ],
